        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 17 at 8:48PM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>At 848 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms 8 miles south of Marshall, or near Leicester, moving
northeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Marshall, Downtown Asheville, North Asheville, Woodfin, Weaverville,
Mars Hill, Leicester, B.R. Parkway-East Asheville To Craggy Gardens,
UNC-Asheville, and Enka.
</description>
        <instruction>Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
